# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the european union mediator carl bildt on thursday predicted the situation in bosnia would get `` more complicated in the immediate future '' and held out little hope for progress on political talks between the country 's warring parties .
# ::alignments
(a / and
      :op1 (p / predict-01
            :ARG0 (p2 / person
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Carl"
                        :op2 "Bildt")
                  :ARG0-of (m / mediate-01)
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (o / organization
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "European"
                                    :op2 "Union"))))
            :ARG1 (c / complicate-01
                  :ARG1 (s / situation
                        :location (c2 / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Bosnia")))
                  :time (f / future
                        :mod (ii / immediate))
                  :ARG2-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                        :ARG1 s
                        :ARG3 (m2 / more)))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / thursday)))
      :op2 (h3 / hold-out-09
            :ARG0 p2
            :ARG1 (h4 / hope-01
                  :ARG0 p2
                  :ARG1 (p3 / progress-01
                        :ARG1 (t2 / talk-01
                              :ARG0 (p4 / party
                                    :ARG0-of (w / war-01)
                                    :poss c2)
                              :mod (p5 / politics)))
                  :quant (l / little))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok stocks finished mixed wednesday after consumer prices showed a larger-than-expected increase in january and minutes from the federal reserve 's last meeting showed the central bank considered but decided against taking a more dovish tone on the threat of inflation .
# ::alignments
(f / finish-01
      :ARG1 (s / stock)
      :ARG2 (m / mix-01)
      :time (w / wednesday)
      :time (a / after
            :op1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s2 / show-01
                        :ARG0 (p / price-01
                              :ARG2 (p2 / person
                                    :ARG0-of (c / consume-01)))
                        :ARG1 (ii / increase-01
                              :ARG1 (m2 / monetary-quantity
                                    :ARG2-of p))
                        :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                              :ARG2 (l / large)
                              :ARG3 (m3 / more)
                              :ARG4 (t / thing
                                    :ARG1-of (e / expect-01)))
                        :time (d / date-entity
                              :month 1)))
            :op2 (s3 / show-01
                  :ARG0 (m4 / minutes
                        :source (m5 / meet-03
                              :ARG0 (r / reserve
                                    :mod (f2 / federal))
                              :mod (l2 / last)))
                  :ARG1 (c2 / consider-02
                        :ARG0 (b / bank
                              :mod (c3 / central))
                        :ARG1-of (c4 / contrast-01
                              :ARG2 (d2 / decide-01
                                    :ARG0 b
                                    :ARG1 (t2 / take-01
                                          :polarity -
                                          :ARG0 b
                                          :ARG1 (t3 / tone
                                                :mod (d3 / dovish
                                                      :ARG2-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                                                            :ARG1 t3
                                                            :ARG3 (m6 / more)))
                                                :topic (t4 / threaten-01
                                                      :ARG1 (ii2 / inflate-01))))))))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok president barack obama on wednesday vowed to work with lawmakers `` this year '' to repeal the law that bans gays from serving openly in the us military .
# ::alignments
(v / vow-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Barack"
                  :op2 "Obama")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (p2 / president)))
      :ARG1 (w / work-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (r / repeal-01
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1 (l / law
                        :ARG0-of (b / ban-01
                              :ARG1 (s / serve-01
                                    :ARG0 (p3 / person
                                          :ARG1-of (g / gay-01))
                                    :ARG2 (m / military
                                          :mod (c / country
                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "US")))
                                    :ARG1-of (o / open-04)))))
            :ARG3 (p4 / person
                  :ARG0-of (l2 / legislate-01))
            :time (y / year
                  :mod (t / this)))
      :time (w2 / wednesday))

      :time (a / after

                              :ARG2-of h2
                              :ARG1 e

                                    :duration-of r)))))
      :quant 5
      :unit (y2 / year))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok crude oil futures rose modestly wednesday as the us government 's weekly report showed a drop in both crude and distillate stockpiles .
# ::alignments
(r / rise-01
      :ARG1 (f / futures
            :mod (o / oil
                  :mod (c / crude)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (w / wednesday))
      :manner (m / modest)
      :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
            :ARG0 (s / show-01
                  :ARG0 (r2 / report-01
                        :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                              :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01
                                    :ARG1 (c3 / country
                                          :name (n / name
                                                :op1 "United"
                                                :op2 "States"))))
                        :frequency (r3 / rate-entity-91
                              :ARG3 (t / temporal-quantity
                                    :quant 1
                                    :unit (w2 / week))))
                  :ARG1 (d2 / drop-01
                        :ARG1 (s2 / stockpile-01
                              :ARG1 (a / and
                                    :op1 (c4 / crude)
                                    :op2 (d3 / distillate)))))))

# ::id 5 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG0 (a / agency
            :mod (n / news))
      :ARG1 (r2 / receive-01
            :ARG0 (w / woman
                  :age (t / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (y / year))
                  :part (l / leg)
                  :ARG1-of (a2 / amputate-01
                        :ARG2-of (r3 / result-01
                              :ARG1 (e / err-01
                                    :ARG0 (d / doctor))))
                  :part l)
            :ARG1 (m / monetary-quantity
                  :quant 1000000
                  :unit (r4 / ruble))
            :ARG3 (c / compensate-01))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / thursday)))

# ::id 6 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG1 (c / close-02
            :ARG1 (t / thing
                  :ARG2-of (p2 / price-01
                        :ARG1 (s2 / share))
                  :ARG1-of (n / new-01))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t2 / tuesday))
            :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (s3 / soften-01
                        :ARG1 (s4 / stock
                              :mod (l / line
                                    :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                                          :value 2)))
                        :ARG1-of (c3 / cause-01
                              :ARG0 (s5 / sentiment
                                    :location (o2 / overseas)
                                    :ARG0-of (n2 / negative-02)
                                    :ARG1-of (c4 / continue-01))))
                  :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                        :ARG2 (l2 / low-04
                              :ARG1 c)
                        :ARG3 (m / more
                              :quant (p3 / percentage-entity
                                    :value 1))))))

      :ARG1 (a / act-02
            :ARG0 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (p2 / person
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Phillip"
                              :op2 "Defreitas"))
                  :op2 (p3 / person
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Devon"
                              :op2 "Malcolm"))
                  :ARG0-of (s / star-01
                        :ARG1 (t / team
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "England"
                                    :op2 "Test"
                                    :op3 "Cricket"))))
            :ARG1-of (l / legal-02)
            :ARG1-of (c / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (a3 / article
                        :mod (m / magazine)
                        :ARG0-of (q / question-03
                              :ARG1 (c2 / commit-01
                                    :ARG1 (p4 / person
                                          :ARG0-of (p5 / play-01)
                                          :ARG1-of (b / bear-02
                                                :location (f / foreign)))
                                    :ARG2 (t2 / team
                                          :mod (n4 / nation))))))))
